<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued December 21 at 3:16PM HST until December 22 at 6:00AM HST by NWS Honolulu</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY FOR THE BIG ISLAND SUMMITS...
...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM HST WEDNESDAY...
* WHAT...Snow accumulations of up to 3 inches with a slight chance
of freezing rain.
* WHERE...Big Island Summits.
* WHEN...Until 6 AM HST Wednesday.
* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult and driving conditions
will be hazardous.</description>
<instruction>A Winter Weather Advisory means that periods of snow, sleet, or
freezing rain will cause travel difficulties. Be prepared for
slippery roads and limited visibilities and use caution while
driving.</instruction>
